title: fix(): put "use strict" into the closure
body: To allow non strict code to be concatenated together with angular into a single file.

title: Trim arguments
body: It turns out that if you have a function like this: function ( ) { }, Chrome will return the space in the empty parameter list while Firefox will not. This means that the injection lookup will get a string like this: " ", which is not handled in inferInjectionArgs.

title: refactor($sniffer): make $sniffer service private
body:
This service has been accidentaly documented in the past, it should not be considered
to be public api.

I'm also removing fallback to Modernizr since we don't need it.

Breaks any app that depends on this service and its fallback to Modernizr, please
migrate to custom "Modernizr" service:

    module.value('Modernizr', function() { return Modernizr; });

title: fix(init): use jQuery#ready for init if available
chore(module): move files around in preparation for more modules
fix($compile): create new (isolate) scopes for directives on root elements
body:
previously we would not create them and it's causing all kinds of issues and accidental leaks

Closes #817

title: Typo and syntax error in the recent documentation.
body: Typo and syntax error in the recent documentation.

title: feat(jqLite): make injector() and scope() work with the document object
body:
For typical app that has ng-app directive on the html element, we now can do:

angular.element(document).injector() or .injector()
angular.element(document).scope() or .scope()

instead of:

angular.element(document.getElementsByTagName('html')[0]).injector()
...
